installed cookie cutter
$ pip3 install --user cookiecutter
added export PATH=$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH to ~/.zshrc
cloned cookiecutter-data-science
$ cookiecutter https://github.com/drivendata/cookiecutter-data-science
named it as wccli
created a new virtualenvironment see https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0cGltFJDUFM
$ mkvirtualenv wccli
installed python3-click into wccli
$ sudo apt-get install python3-click
installed binaryornot into wccli
$ pip3 install binaryornot
installed wordcounter.py with setup.py using 
$ pip3 install --editable .
copied in gettysburg.txt & ran
$ wordcounter gettysburg.txt
cd ~/wccli
$ git init
$ git add .
git commit
create new repository called wccli at my github repo
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/paddy10tellys/wccli.git
git push origin master --force 
nb user name is paddy10tellys p/w = **p1**c**

